# Composer ↔ Grok collaboration (D-43)

**Dan standing preference (every session / new conv — alwaysApply):** For substantive feature builds, Composer and Grok **deliberate before any implementation**, Grok **agrees** the solution, **Composer alone** writes the code, Grok **checks the uncommitted diff before commit**, then Grok **Ship-Verifies** after push. Not optional for real feature work. Platform parity (D-20/D-32).

## Four-phase loop (one ladder — no duplicate gates)

| Phase | Who | What |
|-------|-----|------|
| **1 — Agree** | Composer proposes → Grok **Solution Verifier** | Peer-deliberate until agreement per `model-gates.mdc` § Solution deliberation (D-36) + § Peer deliberation (D-30). **Before the first edit.** |
| **2 — Implement** | **Composer only** | Code, local build, `verify:*` / Playwright. Grok never implements. |
| **3 — Pre-commit check** | Grok **Build Checker** | Read-only review of **uncommitted** diff vs agreed solution + scope. **PASS required before `git commit`.** |
| **4 — Verify** | Grok | **Ship Verifier** post-push (scope vs agreed solution); **Repair Verifier** on Dan repair intent. Sonnet security gate unchanged for high-risk paths. |

Plain language: **deliberate → Grok agrees → Composer builds → Grok checks before commit → commit/push → Ship Verifier.**

## Implementer lock (hard STOP — Dan 2026-07-23)

Pain: a Grok parent forked itself (`resume: "self"`) and started implementing product code.

- **Composer owns all product/code implementation** (`src/`, `functions/src/`, `public/`, behavior-bearing `scripts/*.mjs`, and any ship that would trigger Ship Verifier paths).
- When the **session parent is not Composer** (e.g. Grok orchestrator), it **MUST** dispatch implementation via `Task({ subagent_type: "generalPurpose", model: "composer-2.5-fast", … })` — **never** implement inline and **never** `resume: "self"` for a product build.
- When the parent **is** already Composer 2.5, it may implement inline after Phase 1 agreement (no nested Composer→Composer required).
- Cross-link: strengthens **D-37** (dispatcher never edits when Composer is available).

## When this applies

- **Default:** Dan work directives / planned code changes that are substantive (T1+ feature work, multi-file, branching approach) — see D-36 trigger in `model-gates.mdc`.
- **Skips for Phase 1 Solution Verifier** (unchanged — do not erase): T0 single-file unambiguous; excluded ship paths; repair/planning/Q&A-owned loops; away items with approach-level approved specs; Critical-Reviewer-subsumed. Label with `solution-verifier: N/A (<reason>)`.
- **Phase 3 Pre-commit check** still runs on substantive ships even when Phase 1 was skipped for T0 **if** the final uncommitted diff is multi-file or clearly branching (same post-hoc falsifiability as Ship Verifier). Pure T0 single-file unambiguous → `build-checker: N/A (T0 single-file unambiguous)`.

## Evidence (mandatory)

| Phase | Report line |
|-------|-------------|
| 1 | `solution-verifier: <task-id>` or `solution-verifier: N/A (<reason>)` |
| 3 | `build-checker: <task-id>` + verdict **PASS** before commit — or `build-checker: N/A (<skip reason>)` |
| 4 | `ship-verifier: <task-id>` or `ship-verifier: N/A (paths excluded)` |

Missing a required line when its trigger fired = **NOT RUN**. Do **not** commit while Phase 3 is NOT RUN or FAIL.

## Authority

Full mechanics: `model-gates.mdc` § Solution deliberation (D-36), § Build Checker (pre-commit), § Peer deliberation (D-30), § Ship Verifier, § Repair loop. This rule states Dan's plain-language mandate; it does **not** add a second verification ladder beyond the phases above.
